\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. A. hermanniae} L., {\i  Sp. Pl.} 720 (1753). Shrub up to 50 cm, with tortuous, woody branches, the ends of the branches becoming spiny. Leaves simple or 3-foliolate; leaflets oblong-spathulate or oblong-obovate, sericeous above, strongly so beneath. Flowers solitary or in axillary fascicles of up to 3 flowers, forming an interrupted raceme. Calyx 3-5 mm, tubular, the teeth triangular, much shorter than the sparsely sericeous tube. Corolla yellow. Seed 1.{\i   Mediterranean region.} Al Bl Co Cr Gr It Ju Sa Si Tu.
\par

