\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. A. henoniana} Cosson ex Batt. in Batt. & Trabut,{\i   Fl. Algér.} ({\i  Dicot.}) 250 (1889) ({\i  A. sericea} Lag., non Willd.). Shrub up to 60 cm, with woody branches. Leaves with 3-5 leaflets, sericeous above and beneath; terminal leaflet larger than the laterals; rhachis winged and somewhat sheathing. Heads terminal, 5- to 8-flowered, subtended by digitate bracts just beneath the flowers. Calyx 5-6·5 mm, tubular-campanulate, hirsute, the teeth triangular-subulate, c. ½ as long as the tube. Corolla yellow. Seed 1. {\i  S. & E. Spain}. Hs.
\par

